Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The eviction policy removes the correct entries—least-recently-used under LRU, least-frequently-used under LFU—when the cache is full.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The eviction algorithm—which entry to remove given LRU or LFU metadata—is deterministic logic testable in isolation. The failure—removing the wrong entry—occurs in the eviction selection logic itself. A unit test that creates cache entries with known metadata (timestamps or access counts) and verifies which entry is removed will catch bugs in the algorithm (off-by-one errors, incorrect comparisons, incorrect data structure updates). In-memory data structures are sufficient.","test_description":"Parametrized test over LRU and LFU strategies. For each strategy: (1) create cache entries with known metadata (timestamps for LRU, access counts for LFU), (2) fill the cache to near capacity, (3) insert a new entry to trigger eviction, (4) verify the evicted entry is the one with least recent use time (LRU) or lowest access count (LFU). Test both single-eviction and multi-eviction scenarios, and verify no data corruption.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Unit tests directly test the eviction selection logic, which is where the failure (removing wrong entry) occurs. The invariant is validated by checking which entry was removed. No external infrastructure is needed; in-memory data structures are sufficient to test the algorithm.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13573,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13573},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":nul